hier alst schip tot Brugge want als de goederen pr: bargie van ostendvoolgaen
soo sijn sij den derden dagh hier, ende wagens van costij directelijck tarderen
3 a 4 dagen, oversulx mijn versoeck is ondermael de meer gemelde packen
voor alles & op alle spoet te depescheren al soude die selfs vooraft tot
oftend doen uijt lossen, want jonge cremers moeten meer geevonceert
worden als die niet noodigh hebbe oversulx doet mij wele
In Antwerpen 8 march
Lop don John Loijd
th
S. in answer to yd of 21: past, do send you here inclosed invoyce & bill oft
loading of 2 packes of tykes N. 10„ 13 aboard adriaen de Raes: they cont. mall
142 p, which are as well assorted, as are to be hadd for mony I have great
reason to incorridge you to accept off all though somich more as yd order
because they are not onelij verij good butt cheaper then any other one
could buy them for you for mony, nay if I would sell them here againe
att present, I could make more for them so do exspect yd apprabation
when I shall then dispose of the valew wanting to pay some monges
in London towards the latter end off aprill, you will finde the 3 seals
& 1¼ greend lead good cheap, so expect that you shall gaine well
by them & the rest, for I could make no less for them here, without
any charges, as I note them free aboard, all the tykes I hadd by mee
were packt, so have pickt out the 2 best for you & in case you please
to send mee the acctt. of sale of these twoo, when they shall be disposed
off shall perhaps keep onely to you & be equally concerned: butt I do not
thinck to finde such a penmy worth a gaine all this approaching
summer, whoever shall endeavour to finde goods, as cheap as
possible, whilst I exspect yd answer att the returne of the post
for in case you do not accept off all, shall advise you where
to deliver them for be confident I gott by last post more orders
then goods being now quite without one pas to the legaturen I have
writt the needfull about them & exspect answer p first whilst
I hope to dispatch the same speedly tis a strangs thing what demand
there is att present for that com for francs & other places, yett shall
endeavour to loose N. longertime & serve you to content whilst
In Antwarp 8 march
rest
London Henry Maynard
S my last to you was on the 4 curitt. to which referre you as, also in
th
answer to yd of 21 past as to which the bill I drew on you att 2 uso
shall without faile rembourse you before dewday & give you dew
content for what goods you procvide for mee & in case you dew content
for what goods my last be not to yd content write mee plainly the
needfull, for I will not oblige you to any thinck against yd inclination
& supose casely to finde out the way to drive my trade up on my owne
without to preiudice others by under selling or punctuallitie
in payement & Bloch & Devos are well arrived, the bale N.5 is
indifferent well assorted & for what you provide more, send no
more graijes butt what you might have al ready bought & odd
some mode drapp cullours of a lovely pleasant light mixture
in steed of grayes & in case any oportunitie of hipping for Rotterd
lett one bale come that way to Joan Vandermeulen to follow
my order, besides in case John nelson begon from hull & that
a vessel be ready for Rotterdam lett our desired northrens be sent that
way to sind vandermeulen as for the mocks I tought there abare
non butt black, which I desire or browne much as to cottons lett
them aye by till further order wantingh some more whites of
23 a 25 pence a goud of which please to provide some more att least
10 a 12 double peeces & here after shall order how to packt them
whilst met francine with hindesalen
London will Scawen
In Antwerpen 8 march
Sr. my last to you was on the 1. curitt then desired you to provide & l att
the east india sale 200 salempores of 12:6 a 13 st a ƒ to be dyed as I shall
order p next, besides 50 p of a fines sort thought browne, for our people
will have them finer because theest ware very cours & much courser
then our first parcell, to buy also 60 or 70: p: long cloth of pN. x2 of 29:6
in case yyou could have the browne for that price itt would be better for
the browne are most demanded here, because wee have those that ducti
them & do not well know how the keep the withned from spotting so
leave toy on to do as best you shall finde for both our sadvantidge
mr. maynard shall buy cottons & then shall order how to dispose of
goods desired I hope you shall finde the goods cheap to content & in case
you be not in corridge buy oot her the less & so remane
In Antwerpen 9 mee
Brussel Judocus De sadelier
mons. in antwoort aenden ul van 6 deser segge als dat de weirde
voor ul remise van drij hondert guldens hebbe ontfangen in het
eijnde van dese weeke sal, mijn goet soo goet gelieft sonder twijffel
alhier wesen de sortering is groot, soo dat het best waer ul eensooe
quam al was omtegen heden & aghtdagen dat is naert sondagh
hier te wesen, want het is bij na on mogelijk van ider laken
stael & prijs te senden vermidts de menighte en meest al vers
goot vandat season, want ick schick maer eerst ontrent de
golde weeke tot Brussel te wesen soo sal ul oft ul brief verwagh

den 8 deser was aen ul my ick losten sedert den ue van ditto ontfangen
als mede de 2 stoff packen en N.36, ul had wel gelvenst N 23 miede had
gekomen doch nan verwaght het cceep, en arriverende sal de leade examen
tidt
ick had ul gear donnert omdat adroiteur te senden, maer tot mijncordese
dewan, want mijn intente was dat pr wage nest 6 arg iste laten
komen oelijk N. tren 22, en had ie heden geleden & daeren geseint ten saud
net de reste niet gesonken hebben, oock mett sijndenander hier gelieutt
hebben, dochpatient ie eul alleersije versocht ee packen p vorrgn
degressen vant ben daer omseeer verheegen verom N8:3 dese
hepe morgen oft oer margen suln e wesen, te belaende tsellve
ren commodeveende calnie torgelejt die daer naer waght en
